sense.name: pull out
sense.examples: She had her wisdom teeth extracted. Mom used tweezers to extract the splinter.

sense.name: obtain from within a source
sense.examples: The technology will be able to complete online forms and extract the data returned on a results page. Stir until the ice has melted, then extract the aqueous suspension with petroleum ether. It can then extract the topic structure of a group of related topics. We extracted some interesting linguistic data from the native informant. I extracted a promise from the Dean for two new positions.

sense.name: reason, deduce
sense.examples: In such a manner I extracted the principles that were most beneficial for interaction design. We have extracted the ideas from the unfamiliar words and their strange arrangement.

sense.name: take from a (literary) work, to cite or copy
sense.examples: These are her own words extracted from an interview for the French television. This brief biography and the accompanying images have been extracted from Flames in the Field.

sense.name: calculate the root of a number
sense.examples: This method uses the Newton method to extract the root.
